recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain 2021-2022 F-150 vehicles.  Underbody heat and noise insulators may loosen and contact the aluminum driveshaft, which could damage the driveshaft and cause it to fracture.
recalls.Consequence: A fractured driveshaft can cause a loss of drive power, or a loss of vehicle control if the driveshaft contacts the ground.  Additionally, unintended movement could occur while parked if the parking brake is not engaged.  Any of these scenarios can increase the risk of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: Dealers will inspect and repair the driveshaft as necessary, and properly attach the underbody insulators, free of charge.  Owner notification letters were mailed February 4, 2022.  Owners may contact Ford customer service at 1-866-436-7332.  Ford's number for this recall is 21S56.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.nhtsa.gov.

recalls.Component: ELECTRICAL SYSTEM: INTEGRATED TRAILER BRAKE CONTROL
recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain 2021-2022 F-150, 2022 Maverick, Expedition, Lincoln Navigator, F-250, F-350, F-450, and F-550 vehicles.  Due to a software error, a towed trailer equipped with an electric or electric-over hydraulic brake system may not brake.
recalls.Consequence: Loss of trailer brake functionality could result in extended stopping distance, increasing the risk of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: Dealers will update the integrated trailer brake control module software, free of charge.  Owner notification letters were mailed April 22, 2022.  Owners may contact Ford customer service at 1-866-436-7332.  Ford's number for this recall is 22S17.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.nhtsa.gov.

recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain 2022 F-150 vehicles.  The power-adjustable telescoping steering column connector wiring may be too short.  Wiring that is too short can become damaged or separate if the adjustable steering column is extended all the way.
recalls.Consequence: Damaged or separated wiring may result in the steering column not moving as intended in certain crash conditions, increasing the risk of injury in a crash.
recalls.Remedy: Dealers will inspect the steering column wiring harness and repair the wiring, as necessary, free of charge.  Interim owner notification letters informing owners of the safety risk, were mailed on May 9, 2022.  Owner notification letters were mailed July 28, 2022.  Remedy parts are expected to be available by the end of July, 2022.  Owners may contact Ford customer service at 1-866-436-7332.  Ford's number for this recall is 22S24.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.nhtsa.gov.

recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain 2021-2022 F-150 vehicles.  Underbody heat and noise insulators may loosen and contact the aluminum driveshaft, which could damage the driveshaft and cause it to fracture.
recalls.Consequence: A fractured driveshaft can cause a loss of drive power, or a loss of vehicle control if the driveshaft contacts the ground.  Additionally, unintended movement could occur while parked if the parking brake is not engaged.  Any of these scenarios increases the risk of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: Dealers will inspect and repair the driveshaft, as necessary, and properly attach the underbody insulators, free of charge.  Owner notification letters were mailed September 1, 2022.  Owners may contact Ford customer service at 1-866-436-7332.  Ford's number for this recall is 22S53.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.nhtsa.gov.

recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain 2022 F-150 Raptor Series vehicles equipped with 37-inch tires.  The lug nuts on the wheels may have been incorrectly tightened.
recalls.Consequence: Incorrectly tightened wheel lug nuts can loosen and result in wheel separation from the vehicle, increasing the risk of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: Dealers will tighten or replace the wheel lug nuts, as necessary, free of charge.  Owner notification letters were mailed September 26, 2022.  Owners may contact Ford customer service at 1-866-436-7332.  Ford's number for this recall is 22S59.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.nhtsa.gov.

recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain 2022-2023 Bronco Sport and 2022 F-150 vehicles.  The parking lights may flicker when the headlights are activated.  As such, these vehicles fail to comply with the requirements of Federal Motor Vehicle Safety Standard number 108, "Lamps, Reflective Devices, and Associated Equipment."
recalls.Consequence: Flickering parking lights can reduce visibility, increasing the risk of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: Dealers will replace the LED Driver module, free of charge.  Owner notification letters were mailed March 29, 2023.  Owners may contact Ford customer service at 1-866-436-7332.  Ford's number for this recall is 22C22.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.nhtsa.gov.

recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain 2022 F-150 vehicles.  The right-side instrument panel cover may have been manufactured incorrectly, which can cause the air bag to not deploy as intended.  As such, these vehicles fail to comply with the requirements of Federal Motor Vehicle Safety Standard number 208, "Occupant Crash Protection."
recalls.Consequence: During air bag deployment, the air bag cover my break and project fragments into the vehicle, or the air bag may deploy improperly, increasing the risk of occupant injury.
recalls.Remedy: Dealers will replace the right-side instrument panel cover, free of charge.  Owner notification letters were mailed October 26, 2022.  Owners may contact Ford customer service at 1-866-436-7332.  Ford's number for this recall is 22C23.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.nhtsa.gov.

recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain 2021-2022 F-150 vehicles.  The front windshield wiper motor may become inoperative, causing the wipers to fail.
recalls.Consequence: Inoperative windshield wipers can reduce visibility in certain conditions, increasing the risk of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: Dealers will replace the front windshield wiper motor, free of charge.  Owner notification letters were mailed June 30, 2023.  Remedy parts are expected in the 3rd Quarter of 2023.  Owners may contact Ford customer service at 1-866-436-7332.  Ford's number for this recall is 22S71.  This recall expands previous recall number 22V-142.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.nhtsa.gov.

recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain 2022-2023 F-150, Mustang, Explorer, Bronco, and 2023 Lincoln Aviator vehicles equipped with automatic transmissions.  The transmission may contain a loose bolt which could prevent the transmission from engaging the park gear, although the gear shifter position may indicate that the vehicle has been shifted to "PARK."
recalls.Consequence: The inability to secure the vehicle in the park position can result in a rollaway, increasing the risk of a crash or injury.
recalls.Remedy: Dealers will inspect and, if necessary, replace the transmissions, free of charge.  Owner notification letters were mailed April 25, 2023.  Owners may contact Ford customer service at 1-866-436-7332.  Ford's number for this recall is 23S06.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.nhtsa.gov.

recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain 2021-2023 F-150 vehicles equipped with a single exhaust system.  Contact with the rear axle housing may damage the wiring harness, causing the electric parking brake to activate unexpectedly.
recalls.Consequence: Unexpected activation of the electric parking brake while driving increases the risk of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: Dealers will install a protective tie strap, tape wrap, and replace the harness as necessary, free of charge. Owner notification letters were mailed February 12, 2024.  Owners may contact Ford customer service at 1-866-436-7332.  Ford's number for this recall is 23S35.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.nhtsa.gov.

recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain 2022 F-150 vehicles.  The parking lights may flicker when the headlights are activated.  As such, these vehicles fail to comply with the requirements of Federal Motor Vehicle Safety Standard number 108, "Lamps, Reflective Devices, and Associated Equipment."
recalls.Consequence: Flickering parking lights can reduce visibility, increasing the risk of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: Dealers will update the LED driver module software, free of charge.  Owner notification letters were mailed January 19, 2024.  Owners may contact Ford customer service at 1-866-436-7332.  Ford's number for this recall is 23C36.  Vehicles with high series headlamps previously recalled under recall number 22V-686 that received an incomplete remedy, or have not yet been repaired, will need to have the new remedy completed.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.nhtsa.gov.

recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain 2021-2023 F-150 vehicles equipped with the Trailer Tow Max Duty package and a 9.75-inch heavy duty axle with a 3/4 float axle design.  The rear axle hub bolt may fatigue and break, which can result in damage to the axle hub splines.
recalls.Consequence: Damaged axle hub splines can result in a vehicle rollaway when the vehicle is in park without the parking brake applied or cause a loss of drive power.  Both of these conditions can increase the risk of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: Dealers will replace the left and right rear axle shaft assemblies, free of charge.  Owner notification letters were mailed on May 9, 2025.  Owners may contact Ford customer service at 1-866-436-7332.  Ford's number for this recall is 23S65.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.nhtsa.gov.

recalls.Component: ENGINE AND ENGINE COOLING:ENGINE:HARD PARTS INTERNAL/MECHANICAL
recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain 2021-2022 Bronco, F-150, Edge, Explorer, Lincoln Nautilus, and Lincoln Aviator vehicles equipped with either a 2.7L or 3.0L Nano EcoBoost engine.  The engine intake valves may break while driving, which can result in engine failure and a loss of drive power.
recalls.Consequence: A loss of drive power increases the risk of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: Dealers will perform an engine cycle test and replace the engine as necessary, free of charge. Owner notification letters were mailed July 3, 2025. Owners may contact Ford customer service at 1-866-436-7332.  Ford's number for this recall is 24S55.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.safercar.gov.

recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain 2022 F-150 vehicles.  The parking lights may flicker when the headlights are activated.  As such, these vehicles fail to comply with the requirements of Federal Motor Vehicle Safety Standard number 108, "Lamps, Reflective Devices, and Associated Equipment."
recalls.Consequence: Flickering parking lights can reduce visibility, increasing the risk of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: Dealers will replace the LED Driver module, free of charge.  Owner notification letters were mailed on March 10, 2025.  Owners may contact Ford customer service at 1-866-436-7332.  Ford's number for this recall is 24C30.  These vehicles were previously recalled for this same issue under 22V-686 and will need to have the new remedy performed.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.nhtsa.gov.

recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain 2020-2025 Explorer, Lincoln Aviator, 2020-2024 Escape, Lincoln Corsair, 2018-2024 F-150, Expedition and Lincoln Navigator vehicles.  The air bag warning label may be missing from the dashboard.  As such, these vehicles fail to comply with the requirement Federal Motor Vehicle Safety Standard number 208, "Occupant Crash Protection."
recalls.Consequence: Without a label that shows the proper restraint usage guidelines, the occupants may have an increased risk of injury in the event of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: Ford will mail owners the warning labels, free of charge.  Owner notification letters were mailed December 19, 2024.  Owners may call Ford customer service at 1-866-436-7332.  Ford's number for this recall is 24C39.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153) or go to nhtsa.gov.

recalls.Component: ELECTRICAL SYSTEM: INTEGRATED TRAILER BRAKE CONTROL
recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain 2021-2022 F-150, 2022 Maverick, Expedition, Lincoln Navigator, F-250, F-350, F-450, and F-550 vehicles previously repaired incorrectly under recall number 22V-193.  Due to a software error, a towed trailer equipped with an electric or electric-over hydraulic brake system may not brake.
recalls.Consequence: Loss of trailer brake functionality can extend the distance required to stop, increasing the risk of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: Dealers will update the integrated trailer brake control module software, free of charge.  Owner notification letters were mailed April 11, 2025.  Owners may contact Ford customer service at 1-866-436-7332.  Ford's number for this recall is 25S18.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 888-327-4236 (TTY 888-275-9171) or go to nhtsa.gov.

recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain 2021-2024 Bronco, F-150, 2021-2024 Edge, 2022-2025 Escape, F-250, F-350, F-450, F-550, F-600, 2022-2024 Expedition, 2022-2025 Transit, 2021-2023 Mach-E, 2024 Ranger, Mustang, 2021-2023 Lincoln Nautilus, 2022-2024 Navigator, and 2023-2024 Corsair vehicles. A software error may cause the rearview camera image to delay, freeze, or not display when the vehicle is in reverse.
recalls.Consequence: A frozen or missing rearview camera image can reduce the driver's view behind the vehicle, increasing the risk of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: The accessory protocol interface module (APIM) software will be updated by a dealer or through an over-the-air update, free of charge. This will be a phased campaign, with the remedy becoming available in different phases based on model and model years. Interim letters notifying owners of the safety risk were mailed on June 26, 2025. Additional letters will be mailed once the final remedy is available on each phase. Owner notification letters were sent on October 8, 2025. Owners may contact Ford customer service at 1-866-436-7332. Ford's number for this recall is 25S49.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 888-327-4236 (TTY 888-275-9171) or go to nhtsa.gov.

recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain 2021-2023 Bronco, Explorer, Lincoln Aviator, F-250 SD, F-350 SD, F-450 SD,  F-550 SD, 2021-2022 Lincoln Navigator, Mustang, F-150, and 2022 Expedition vehicles. The low-pressure fuel pump may fail, which can result in an engine stall while driving.
recalls.Consequence: An engine stall increases the risk of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: The remedy is under development. Interim notification letters notifying owners of the safety risk were mailed July 16, 2025. Second letters will be sent once the remedy is available, anticipated March 2026. Owners may contact Ford customer service at 1-866-436-7332. Ford's number for this recall is 25S75.

recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain 2022 F-150 vehicles that were repaired incorrectly under recalls 22V686 and 23V802. The parking lights may flicker when the headlights are activated. As such, these vehicles fail to comply with the requirements of Federal Motor Vehicle Safety Standard number 108, "Lamps, Reflective Devices, and Associated Equipment."
recalls.Consequence: Flickering parking lights can reduce visibility, increasing the risk of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: Dealers will replace the light emitting diode control module and update the software, free of charge. Owner notification letters were mailed August 20, 2025. Owners may contact Ford customer service at 1-866-436-7332. Ford's number for this recall is 25C38.

recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain 2022 F-150 vehicles that were repaired incorrectly under recall 22V686. The parking lights may flicker when the headlights are activated.  As such, these vehicles fail to comply with the requirements of Federal Motor Vehicle Safety Standard number 108, "Lamps, Reflective Devices, and Associated Equipment."
recalls.Consequence: Flickering parking lights can reduce visibility, increasing the risk of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: Dealers will replace the light emitting diode control module and update the software, free of charge. Owner notification letters were mailed September 12, 2025. Owners may contact Ford customer service at 1-866-436-7332. Ford's number for this recall is 25C37.

recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain 2021-2022 Expedition, Lincoln Navigator, 2021-2023 F-150, 2022 F-250 SD, F-350 SD, and F-450 SD vehicles. The moonroof wind deflector clips may be inadequately attached to the moonroof frame, which can result in the wind deflector detaching from the vehicle.
recalls.Consequence: A detached wind deflector can become a road hazard and increase the risk of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: Dealers will inspect and repair the  moonroof wind deflector as necessary, free of charge. Owner notification letters were mailed November 10, 2025. Owners may contact Ford customer service at 1-866-436-7332. Ford's number for this recall is 25SB7. Vehicle Identification Numbers (VINs) involved in this recall will be searchable on NHTSA.gov beginning October 30, 2025.

issues.title: 12V Battery Depletion and Failure
issues.description: The 12V auxiliary battery drains completely when the vehicle sits unused, leaving owners unable to start the truck or access basic functions. This occurs even when the high-voltage battery has charge remaining.
issues.fix_description: Replace 12V battery and update software. Ford has issued software updates to address battery drain issues.
issues.prevention: Keep vehicle plugged in when not in use, avoid extended periods without driving

issues.title: Charging Port Door Malfunction
issues.description: The charging port door fails to open or close properly, sometimes getting stuck in the open position or requiring manual force to operate. This can expose charging components to weather.
symptoms: Error messages related to charging door
issues.fix_description: Replace charging port door actuator mechanism or adjust door alignment
issues.prevention: Keep charging port area clean and free of debris, avoid forcing door operation

issues.title: Software Update Failures and Glitches
issues.description: Over-the-air software updates fail to install properly or cause system malfunctions, including loss of features, display issues, and connectivity problems.
issues.fix_description: Perform factory reset and manual software update at dealership
issues.prevention: Ensure stable internet connection during updates, keep vehicle plugged in during update process

issues.title: Range Loss in Cold Weather
issues.description: Significant reduction in driving range during cold weather conditions, with some owners reporting up to 40-50% range loss compared to EPA estimates in freezing temperatures.
issues.fix_description: No permanent fix available; this is inherent to current battery technology. Pre-conditioning battery while plugged in can help.
issues.prevention: Precondition vehicle while plugged in, park in heated garage when possible, plan for reduced range in winter

issues.title: DC Fast Charging Speed Reduction
issues.description: DC fast charging speeds slower than advertised, with charging rates dropping significantly after initial burst, leading to longer charging sessions than expected.
issues.fix_description: Software updates may improve charging curves; ensure battery is properly conditioned before charging
issues.prevention: Precondition battery before fast charging, avoid charging in extreme temperatures

issues.title: Frunk Water Intrusion
issues.description: Water enters the front trunk (frunk) during heavy rain or car washes, potentially damaging stored items and creating drainage issues.
issues.fix_description: Replace or adjust frunk seals and drainage components
issues.prevention: Avoid storing sensitive items in frunk during rain, check seal condition regularly

issues.title: Mobile Connector Overheating
issues.description: The Ford mobile connector overheats during charging, potentially creating fire hazards and causing charging to stop automatically.
issues.fix_description: Replace mobile connector with updated version, ensure proper electrical connection
issues.prevention: Use Ford Charge Station Pro when possible, ensure outlet is properly wired for load

issues.title: Tailgate Power Functions Failure
issues.description: Power tailgate fails to open or close properly, with electronic controls becoming unresponsive or operating intermittently.
issues.fix_description: Replace tailgate control module or actuator motor, update software
issues.prevention: Keep tailgate area clean, avoid overloading tailgate, regular operation to prevent seizing

issues.title: HVAC System Malfunctions
issues.description: Heating, ventilation, and air conditioning system fails to maintain temperature properly or stops working entirely, affecting cabin comfort and battery range.
symptoms: Excessive battery drain from climate control
issues.fix_description: Replace HVAC control module, check refrigerant levels, update software
issues.prevention: Regular HVAC system maintenance, avoid extreme temperature settings

issues.title: BlueCruise Hands-Free Driving Issues
issues.description: BlueCruise system disengages unexpectedly, provides false warnings, or fails to detect lane markings properly during hands-free driving operation.
symptoms: System not activating when it should
issues.fix_description: Software updates to improve system algorithms, camera calibration may be required
issues.prevention: Keep cameras and sensors clean, ensure proper lane markings are visible

editorial.tagline: America's electric truck revolution has arrived
editorial.hero_blurb: The F-150 Lightning transforms America's best-selling truck into an instant-torque electric powerhouse. Zero emissions meets maximum capability in a package that redefines what pickup performance can be.
editorial.essence: This is the truck that proves electric can be better than gas, delivering face-melting acceleration while maintaining the F-150's legendary capability. It's a paradigm shift wrapped in familiar bodywork that America already loves.
editorial.heritage: Built on the foundation of America's best-selling truck for over four decades, the Lightning represents Ford's boldest evolution of the F-150 nameplate since its 1975 debut.
editorial.design_philosophy: Designers aimed to maintain the F-150's rugged authenticity while integrating electric technology seamlessly, creating a truck that looks familiar but delivers revolutionary performance.
editorial.motorsport_history: While the Lightning nameplate recalls the high-performance SVT F-150 Lightning of the 1990s-2000s, this electric version writes its own chapter in Ford's performance truck legacy.
editorial.engine_character: Twin electric motors deliver instantaneous, silent fury with no lag, no hesitation - just pure, relentless acceleration that pins you to your seat from the moment you touch the throttle.
editorial.transmission_feel: Single-speed direct drive eliminates shifting entirely, providing seamless power delivery that feels more like riding a lightning bolt than driving a traditional truck.
editorial.chassis_dynamics: Independent rear suspension transforms ride quality while the low-mounted battery pack creates a surprisingly planted, car-like center of gravity despite the truck's imposing size.
editorial.steering_feel: Electric power steering offers good road feel with appropriate weight, though the silence amplifies every input and makes precise maneuvering feel more connected than expected.
editorial.brake_confidence: Massive regenerative braking capability combines with traditional friction brakes to provide reassuring stopping power, with adjustable regen levels for different driving preferences.
editorial.sound_signature: Near-silent operation broken only by tire noise and wind, with optional artificial sound enhancement for those who miss traditional truck presence.
editorial.ideal_owner: Tech-savvy truck buyers who want maximum capability with zero emissions, early adopters who don't mind charging infrastructure limitations, and anyone who craves instant torque.
editorial.not_ideal_for: Long-haul towers, remote workers without reliable charging access, traditionalists who equate truck authenticity with V8 rumble, or those on tight budgets.
editorial.buyers_summary: The Lightning delivers on electric truck promises with genuine capability and shocking performance. However, charging infrastructure and range limitations mean careful consideration of your specific use case is essential.
pros: Instant torque delivery crushes gas trucks
Maintains full F-150 towing and payload capability
cons: Limited charging infrastructure for long trips
Premium pricing over comparable gas F-150s
best_for: Daily commuting with weekend work capability
